                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.1216M/139.</note>
                <head>[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The embassy has received a note from the foreign office which states that
                    President Diaz has no authority to permit the erection of levees or to grant
                    free entry of materials for the work. The negotiation of a treaty is suggested
                    and the Mexican ambassador at Washington has received detailed and specific
                    instructions as to terms. Congressional action must be taken concerning the free
                    entry of materials.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
